#
# Custom recipe: SGLang v0.5.15.post1 + our SM121 sgl-kernel patches.
#
# THE production 0.5.15.post1-sm121 image, successor to sglang-0.5.15-sm121
# .recipe. Serves nvidia/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4 (NATIVE) AND
# nvidia/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 (NATIVE). Created 2026-07-23.
#
# Pinned to upstream tag `v0.5.15.post1` (released 2026-07-14T08:43Z). The
# sglang-0.5.15-sm121 recipe is kept for rollback.
#
# ── DELTA gegenüber sglang-0.5.15-sm121.recipe ──────────────────────────────
#   1. SGLANG_VERSION 0.5.15 → 0.5.15.post1, SGLANG_REF v0.5.15 → v0.5.15.post1.
#      post1 is a SOURCE-ONLY bugfix release — its pyproject deps are BYTE-
#      IDENTICAL to v0.5.15 (verified: flashinfer 0.6.12 / cutlass-dsl 4.5.2 /
#      transformers 5.12.1 / kernels>=0.14.1,<0.15), so no upstream-pin moves.
#      Content (GitHub release notes, "mostly for GLM 5.2"):
#        • #30454 #30627 Fix DSA model launching on non-Cuda/HIP devices
#        • #30858 Fix flashinfer dependency on Cuda-12 images (we are cu132 →
#          neutral, but harmless)
#        • #31001 Fix NaN outputs caused by flashinfer trtllm FP4 MoE kernels on
#          LONG input — a possible touchpoint for the unresolved GB10 Hy3/HYV3
#          W4A4 NaN (reference_hybrid_uniform_w4a4_nan); different path but worth
#          re-checking on the built image.
#        • #30839 #30992 GLM 5.2 IndexShare on PD-disagg / Context-Parallel
#      None of these touch a file our patches modify (see patch-verify note).
#   2. FLASHINFER_VERSION 0.6.14 → 0.6.15.post1 — the actual DRIVER of this bump.
#      flashinfer 0.6.15 lands explicit GB10/SM12x work directly relevant here:
#        • Gemma 4 + MiniMax-M3 NVFP4 MoE now run natively on Blackwell SM12x
#          (consumer / DGX Spark), via two new NVFP4-MoE activation functions
#          added to the SM12x MoE path — gelu_tanh + swiglu_oai (#3744 #3737).
#          May reduce what the separate gemma4 recipe's source patches carry —
#          RE-EVALUATE the gemma4 image against this base.
#        • Context-parallel GDN linear attention on SM120 (#3659) — relevant for
#          Qwen3.5MoE-linear-attn / GDN models.
#        • TRTLLM-GEN MoE: DeepSeek-V4 hash_topk routing + shared-expert fusion
#          + low-latency FP8 blockwise megakernel (BS<=8) (#2625 #3561 #3424).
#        • Unified MoE API with Expert Parallelism (moe_ep, experimental).
#      See the FLASHINFER_VERSION block below. Roll-back: 0.6.14 (the live-
#      validated 0.5.15-sm121 pin) or upstream 0.6.12.
#   3. CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION 4.6.0 → 4.6.1 — the in-order release-mate for the
#      flashinfer 0.6.15 era (cutlass-dsl 4.6.1 released 2026-07-13, i.e. just
#      before the flashinfer 0.6.15 nightlies of 2026-07-17+). flashinfer 0.6.15
#      STILL constrains cutlass-dsl only `>=4.5.0` (open-ended, same as 0.6.14),
#      so the wheel-swap ICE risk (reference_cutlass_dsl_wheel_swap) persists and
#      the EXPLICIT pin stays mandatory. 4.6.1 is a NEW version number (not a
#      same-version wheel-content swap), so lower risk than the 4.5.2 incident.
#      ⚠️  GPU-VERIFY on the built image before deploy (the rmsnorm smoke test
#         below) — I cannot validate the 0.6.15/4.6.1 pairing off-GPU. Conservative
#         fallback if 4.6.1 ICEs: 4.6.0 (the known-good 0.5.15-sm121 mate), then
#         4.5.1 (last pre-swap release). See CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION block.
#   4. TRANSFORMERS_VERSION + KERNELS_VERSION UNCHANGED (5.12.1 / 0.14.1) — post1's
#      pyproject pins them identically to v0.5.15; do NOT bump past the SGLang ref
#      (no inference-hot-path benefit; kernels carries a hard <0.15 constraint and
#      the only hub kernel, sgl-flash-attn3, is hard-disabled on GB10 anyway).
#   5. DSV4 EAGLE-MTP marlin + TileLang 0.1.8 indexer compat: STILL needed on GB10
#      (APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG kept at 1) — unchanged rationale from the
#      0.5.15 recipe; both source patches re-verified clean against post1 (below).
#
# ── PATCH VERIFY (2026-07-23, non-GPU) ──────────────────────────────────────
#   Since post1 is source-only, the ONLY correctness question is whether our
#   patches still apply. They do:
#     • The two ACTIVE source patches were DRY-RUN clean against the actual
#       v0.5.15.post1 source (raw.githubusercontent, `patch -p1 --dry-run`):
#         - sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch → Hunk #1 at 1385 (offset -61)
#         - sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch → both hunks (offset -16)
#       IDENTICAL offsets to the v0.5.15 run → the target files
#       (modelopt_quant.py, dsa/tilelang_kernel.py) are byte-identical v0.5.15.
#     • The GitHub compare v0.5.15...v0.5.15.post1 changed 28 files; NONE is a
#       target of ANY patch this recipe applies. sgl-kernel patch targets
#       (sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt, jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh)
#       and the Dockerfile patches (scitrera Dockerfile.sglang-nightly, not the
#       sglang repo) are untouched. The in-container `patch --dry-run` gate in
#       build_sm121_image.sh stays the backstop for any drift.
#
# ── Runtime patches now UPSTREAM in v0.5.15+ (drop from sglang_launch.sh) ─────
#   • Hunyuan Hy3/HYV3 special-token suffix (PR #29920, in v0.5.15) → the
#     `_sgl_hunyuan_token_suffix_` backport block in sglang_launch.sh is dead
#     code on this image (grep guard makes it a no-op; deletable when this image
#     is the pinned one). LAUNCH-SCRIPT concern, not a recipe patch — listed only
#     so the image bump and script cleanup stay coordinated.
#
# RUNTIME CAVEAT (unchanged): the DSV4 NVFP4 path default-routes to
# moe_runner_backend=flashinfer_trtllm_routed which is not runnable on SM121
# (#26324). The DSV4 model profiles pin flashinfer_cutlass explicitly.
#
# Voraussetzungen: xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132 Base
# auf spark4 (scripts/build_pytorch_base_image.sh, siehe
# ensure_base_image_present in build_sm121_image.sh). Base UNVERÄNDERT ggü.
# 0.5.15 — kein pytorch-base-Rebuild nötig (torch/cuda/nccl unberührt).
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
TARGET=runtime

BASE_IMAGE=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132

# Override über den v0.5.15.post1-Upstream-Pin (flashinfer_python[cu13]==0.6.12)
# hinaus auf 0.6.15.post1 (stable, released 2026-07-21). 0.6.15 bringt explizite
# GB10/SM12x-Erweiterungen (siehe DELTA-Note 2): Gemma-4 + MiniMax-M3 NVFP4-MoE
# nativ auf SM12x (neue gelu_tanh/swiglu_oai NVFP4-MoE-Activations), SM120
# context-parallel GDN, TRTLLM-GEN MoE DeepSeek-V4 hash_topk. Bewusst gepaart mit
# cutlass-dsl 4.6.1 unten (in-order release-mate der 0.6.15-Ära). post1's
# pyproject pinnt WEITERHIN 0.6.12, der Override bleibt also nötig.
# Roll-back-Optionen: 0.6.14 (bekannt-gut auf 0.5.15-sm121) oder 0.6.12 (Upstream).
# FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.14
# FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.12
FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.15.post1

# transformers 5.12.1 — exakt SGLang v0.5.15.post1s pyproject-Pin (==5.12.1,
# unverändert ggü. v0.5.15). NICHT isoliert über die SGLang-Ref hinaus bumpen
# (kein Perf-Nutzen — transformers ist nicht im Inferenz-Hot-Path; PyPI-latest ist
# 5.14.1, irrelevant). HINWEIS: der get_config()-sub_configs-Patch in
# sglang_launch.sh war gegen die transformers-5.5.0-Regression geschrieben; gegen
# 5.12.1 verhält er sich per grep-Guard als No-op falls gefixt — auf dem gebauten
# Image gegenprüfen.
TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.12.1

# kernels 0.14.1 — exakt SGLang v0.5.15.post1s pyproject-Pin (kernels>=0.14.1,
# <0.15, unverändert ggü. v0.5.15; PyPI-latest 0.16.0 verletzt das <0.15-Constraint
# und ist irrelevant). PERF-NEUTRAL für SM121: der einzige hub-geladene
# SGLang-Kernel (sgl-flash-attn3) ist auf GB10 hart deaktiviert (_is_fa3_supported
# → major==9||8, GB10 ist major==12) und hat keine sm_121/ARM64-Builds; der
# SM121-Hotpath läuft über das kompilierte sgl-kernel + flashinfer, nicht über den
# HF-Hub. 0.14.1 (nicht open-ended): 0.14.0 hat einen breaking repo-type-change,
# 0.14.1 ist der Bugfix.
KERNELS_VERSION=0.14.1

# nvidia-cutlass-dsl 4.6.1 — explicit pin, force-reinstalled late in the build
# (empty = no-op). flashinfer 0.6.15 requires only >=4.5.0 (open-ended, unchanged
# from 0.6.14) AND NVIDIA has shipped different wheel content under the same
# version number before (the 2026-07-06 4.5.2 variant + 4.5.3 both ICE on every
# fresh CuTe-DSL JIT compile — mlir_global_dtors 'data' kwarg / GPUModuleOp
# TypeError; full post-mortem in the 0.5.14 recipe delta 7 + reference_cutlass_
# dsl_wheel_swap), so the explicit pin stays mandatory. 4.6.1 (2026-07-13) is the
# in-order successor to 4.6.0 (CuTe-DSL bugfixes: issues #3243/#3359/#3365/#3312,
# Thor 12.9-wheel compile, FA-v2 Ampere regression) and the natural release-mate
# for the flashinfer 0.6.15 nightlies (2026-07-17+). It is a NEW version number,
# not a same-version wheel swap, so lower risk than the 4.5.2 incident.
# ⚠️  MUST GPU-verify on the built image before deploy (rmsnorm smoke test below).
# Conservative fallback if 4.6.1 misbehaves: 4.6.0 (known-good 0.5.15-sm121 mate),
# then 4.5.1 (last pre-swap release).
# CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION=4.6.0
# CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION=4.5.1
CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION=4.6.1
#
# GPU smoke test after build (must NOT raise the GPUModuleOp TypeError /
# mlir_global_dtors ICE):
#   python -c "import flashinfer, torch; \
#     from flashinfer.norm import rmsnorm; \
#     x=torch.randn(4,512,device='cuda',dtype=torch.bfloat16); \
#     w=torch.randn(512,device='cuda',dtype=torch.bfloat16); \
#     print(rmsnorm(x,w).shape)"
# Wired via dockerfile-cutlass-dsl-pin.patch (build_sm121_image.sh step 2-cutlass).

# Audio multimodal deps — installed by dockerfile-audio-deps.patch (gated ARG,
# empty = no-op). Required for omni models that decode audio at runtime, e.g.
# nvidia/Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni-30B-A3B-Reasoning-NVFP4 (SGLang nano_nemotron_vl.py
# get_audio_feature → librosa; upstream SGLang does NOT install it). librosa pulls
# soundfile/audioread/numba/llvmlite as deps. Text + image/video work without this;
# only AUDIO input needs it. Empty/remove to drop the audio stack from the image.
AUDIO_DEPS="librosa"

# accelerate — baked into the image (was a runtime `pip install` in
# sglang_launch.sh). SGLang's ModelOptModelLoader (_load_modelopt_base_model)
# imports it; the upstream base image omits it, so GLM-5-NVFP4 and any
# EAGLE/speculative-decode target with a modelopt-quantized base ImportError
# without it. Installed by dockerfile-accelerate.patch (gated ARG, default
# "accelerate"). The launch-script `import accelerate || pip install` guard
# stays as belt-and-suspenders for non-baked images and becomes a fast no-op
# here. Set empty to opt out (unset also defaults to "accelerate" — the ARG
# default in the Dockerfile patch).
ACCELERATE_DEPS="accelerate"

SGLANG_VERSION=0.5.15.post1
SGLANG_REF="v0.5.15.post1"

# main-ahead sgl-kernel patch variant. The mscclpp link refactor (dropped
# mscclpp_static from the common_ops_sm90/sm100 link lines + removed the
# mscclpp-build block) that first broke sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch on
# v0.5.14 is STILL present in v0.5.15.post1. This flag makes build_sm121_image.sh
# install the "-mainahead" patch siblings under their canonical names where they
# exist (currently skip-sm90-target, disable-fa3). The other sgl-kernel patches
# have no -mainahead sibling and are applied canonically; the in-container dry-run
# gates all of them. sgl-kernel patch targets (CMakeLists.txt,
# nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh) are UNCHANGED v0.5.15...post1 → the 2026-07-12
# clean-apply verification against v0.5.15 carries over. Drop this flag only if a
# future SGLANG_REF predates the mscclpp refactor.
SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1

# ── DeepSeek-V4 FlashMLA kernel: DROPPED (native SM120/121 since v0.5.13) ─────
# PR #24692 (in v0.5.13+, still in v0.5.15.post1) ships a native SM120/121
# sparse-decode path; the 0xSero vendored sm_121a kernel + stock-flash_mla install
# are redundant (UPSTREAM_DSV4_BUGS.md §8, walls 0+6). Empty values skip the step.
FLASH_MLA_REPO=
FLASH_MLA_REF=
DSV4_KERNEL_REPO=
DSV4_KERNEL_REF=
DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH=

# ── DeepSeek-V4 NVFP4 MoE: NATIVE since v0.5.14 (PR #25820 merged) → OFF ──────
# PR #25820 merged upstream 2026-06-22, in v0.5.14/v0.5.15/post1. Set to 0:
# re-applying a merged patch fails the in-container dry-run and aborts the build.
# The DSV4 profiles still serve off this image natively.
APPLY_DSV4_NVFP4_PR25820=0

# ── DeepSeek-V4 EAGLE-MTP marlin branch + TileLang 0.1.8 indexer compat → ON ─
# Verified in-source at v0.5.15.post1 (via dry-run, 2026-07-23): the native
# HybridFp8NvFp4Config.get_quant_method STILL hardcodes the MTP/nextn draft MoE
# layers to Mxfp4FlashinferTrtllmMoEMethod (SM100-only TVM kernel) — no marlin
# branch — so nvidia/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4's speculative_enabled: true /
# speculative_moe_runner_backend: marlin still crashes on GB10 as shipped. The
# companion dsa/tilelang_kernel.py 1D alloc_shared bug (breaks
# SGLANG_OPT_USE_TILELANG_INDEXER on TileLang 0.1.8) likewise persists. Both are
# small GB10-only remainders. Gates dockerfile-dsv4-mtp-marlin-tilelang.patch in
# build_sm121_image.sh::apply_patches. Applies TWO source patches:
# sglang-dsv4-mtp-marlin-v0.5.14.patch (modelopt_quant.py) +
# sglang-tilelang-018-indexer-compat.patch (dsa/tilelang_kernel.py).
# ✅ Both re-VERIFIED to apply clean against the v0.5.15.post1 source in a non-GPU
#    dry-run 2026-07-23 (identical offsets -61 / -16 to the v0.5.15 run → target
#    files byte-identical). No rebase needed; the in-container dry-run gate stays
#    the backstop for future drift.
# Non-spec (no MTP) DSV4 serving is UNAFFECTED either way (native, no gate).
# Drop to 0 / delete once both fixes land upstream (marlin branch in SGLang,
# TileLang >=0.1.9 with the inject_permuted_layout 1D-shared fix).
APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG=1

# ── Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4: MERGED upstream (PR #27906) → OFF ──────────
# PR #27906 (+ cookbook #29905) merged and shipped since the v0.5.15 tag.
# v0.5.15.post1's modelopt_quant.py natively handles the "W4A16_NVFP4"
# MIXED_PRECISION path Qwen3.6 needs. Set to 0: re-applying a merged patch fails
# the in-container dry-run and aborts the build.
# ⚠️  The OPEN dispatch fix #28099 (detect MIXED_PRECISION by content) is a RUNTIME
#     patch in sglang_launch.sh, unaffected by this flag — re-validate Qwen3.6 on
#     the live model; the launch-script model_config.py routing patch may still be
#     needed until #28099 merges.
APPLY_QWEN36_MIXED_NVFP4_PR27906=0

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.15.post1-sm121
